title: Grant Wood American Gothic Keychain
description:
Keychain developed from Grant Wood’s American Gothic, 1930, from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Grant Wood is known for his stylized and subtly humorous scenes of rural people, Iowa cornfields, and mythic subjects from American history—such as the Art Institute’s iconic painting American Gothic, 1930.

A great gift for yourself of a friend.

  • Dimensions of charm: 1.125 x 1.75 x .125 in.
  • Materials: Brass with colored enamel.
